Bevölkerung; control in nominal context? Some people think that nouns don't allow raising, but some derived nouns in English do (cf. Alexiadou, t.a.)). It seems that das Potential der Islamisten, die Bevölkerung einzuschüchtern ?!= das Potenzial der Bevölkerung von den Islamisten eingeschüchtert zu werden and Es hat das Potential zu regnen seems to be rather odd, which speaks for a control analysis… If it should turn out that this is an instance of raising, this has far-reaching theoretical consequences: At least since Chomsky's (1970) Remarks on Nominalization nobody believes that raising is possible with nouns (although recently it has been claimed that this doesn't hold for derived nouns, cf. (Alexiadou, 2020)) and there are even syntactic theories (e.g. TAG) where this doesn't have to be stipulated but is built into the theory.
